The '''Young Trophy''' is the annual inter-institution sporting competition for young engineers. The event was first held in 1933 when a joint team from the [[Institution of Mechanical Engineers]] and the [[Institution of Civil Engineers]] challenged the [[Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers]] (now part of the [[Institution of Engineering and Technology]]) to a cricket and tennis match.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.theiet.org/resources/library/archives/featured/young-trophy.cfm |title=The Young Cricket Trophy |work= |publisher=[[Institution of Engineering and Technology]] |accessdate=13 April 2014}}</ref> Subsequent tournaments have been contested over a range of sports such as football, badminton, volleyball, basketball and dodgeball.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://nearyou.imeche.org/near-you/UK/Greater-London/Greater-London-Young-Member-Panel/event-detail?id=4049 |title=The Young Trophy 2010 |work= |publisher=[[Institution of Mechanical Engineers]] |accessdate=13 April 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ileve.org/index.cfm?go=page.view&item=3218 |title=CIBSE Young Trophy 2013  |work= |publisher=[[Chartered Institution of Building Services Engineers]] |accessdate=13 April 2014}}</ref> The participants have also expanded beyond the original three institutions with teams from [[Royal Institute of British Architects]] and [[Chartered Institution of Building Services Engineers]] competing in 2013.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://nearyou.imeche.org/docs/default-source/Greater-London-Young-Member-Panel/youngs-trophy-20135AA01C0DFB4A.pdf?sfvrsn=0 |title=Youngs Trophy 2013  |work= |publisher=[[Institution of Mechanical Engineers]] |accessdate=13 April 2014}}</ref>

